p :::s33:::Their names are Mary , Diana , and St. John -LRB- pronounced `` Sinjin '' -RRB- Rivers , and Jane quickly becomes friends with them .
p :::s34:::St. John is a clergyman , and he finds Jane a job teaching at a charity school in Morton .
p :::s38:::St. John decides to travel to India as a missionary , and he urges Jane to accompany him -- as his wife .
:::s39:::Jane agrees to go to India but refuses to marry her cousin because she does not love him .
:::s40:::St. John pressures her to reconsider , and she nearly gives in .
:::s44:::Jane travels on to Rochester 's new residence , Ferndean , where he lives with two servants named John and Mary .
